{"id":"ev_5a4b1e30e3bb4592","runId":"run_230","type":"delegation","at":1782323622182,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_4672cfb905804c2f","atom":0,"task":"Ticket 0048 — Adopt a minimal ESLint 9 flat config in CoCoder's own engine repo (this repo root). Goal: add a RESTRAINED type-aware linter that catches the class tsc+vitest miss (floating/forgotten promises, unused/dead code, leftover debug, dangerous eval), without creating noise.\n\nWHAT TO DO:\n1. Install dev deps pinned from REAL installs (record the exact resolved versions): eslint 9.x, @typescript-eslint/parser 8.x, @typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin 8.x, and typescript-eslint 8.x (the flat-config meta package) if you use it. Use pnpm at the repo root. Mirror CoBuilder's pins unless a newer 9.x/8.x is deliberately chosen — note which.\n2. Create `eslint.config.mjs` at the repo root: ESLint 9 FLAT config, minimal and type-aware. Reference shape: `CoBuilder/infrastructure/eslint.config.mjs` (read it first — flat config, scoped globs, restrained security rules). Keep the ruleset SMALL and high-signal. Required intent: enable type-aware checking (parserOptions.projectService or project), and turn on the safety/security essentials such as @typescript-eslint/no-floating-promises, no-misused-promises, no-unused-vars (tuned to avoid noise on intentional patterns, e.g. argsIgnorePattern '^_'), and the core no-eval. Do NOT pull in a large stylistic ruleset. Scope ignores appropriately (dist/build/node_modules, generated artifacts, cocoder/runs, local). Match the repo's module/TS setup.\n3. Add a `lint` script to the root package.json (e.g. \"lint\": \"eslint .\"). Run it. The repo MUST PASS lint. Fix real violations at the root cause; if a violation is genuinely out of scope to fix now, scope it out DELIBERATELY and NARROWLY (targeted disable with a reason comment, or a precise ignore) — do NOT weaken a rule into a tautology or disable it globally to go green.\n4. Decide and DOCUMENT whether `lint` joins the CI gate / `pnpm test` flow. State your recommendation and reasoning in your handoff; if you wire it into the test/CI script, show the exact change. (I will verify this decision — surface the tradeoff, don't bury it.)\n\nMUST NOT BREAK: existing `tsc` typecheck, existing vitest suite, the `pnpm test` flow if it already passes. Don't reformat or touch unrelated files. Don't add prettier/biome.\n\nREPORT BACK: the exact installed versions, the full eslint.config.mjs, the package.json script diff, the literal `pnpm lint` output (exit 0), any deliberate scope-outs with their justification, and your CI/test-gate recommendation with reasoning. Write scope: repo-root config + package.json/lockfile + any source files you fix lint violations in."}}
